23/09/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- The OSCE's chairman-in-office, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, said Wednesday (22 September) he would "encourage" the ODIHR to deploy monitors for the November referendum in Macedonia. 
Passy's comment followed talks with Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva in New York. 
Passy and Mitreva also discussed relations between their countries. 
Passy said Skopje could rely on Bulgaria's assistance and expertise in the process of NATO and EU integration. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik- 23/09/04; OSCE Web site, Makfax - 22/09/04)
